        "body": "## Summary\n- replace hardcoded `1.0.0` Windows node/tray handshake version fields with `AppVersionInfo.Version`\n- add a node-only startup reconnect path for already-paired Windows nodes that only have a persisted `NodeDeviceToken`\n- preserve no-downgrade credential precedence, including SSH-tunnel startup and legacy root identity fallback\n- add regression coverage for node-only reconnect, SSH tunnel startup, and startup fallback wiring\n\n## Validation\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` -> clean after accepting two P2 findings\n- Azure live probe before this patch reproduced the restart bug: pending stayed 0 and paired stayed 4, but `connectedCount` dropped to 0 after tray restart because startup had missing/non-durable credentials\n- blocked locally: this macOS pane and the current Windows crabboxes do not have `dotnet`; CI is running the Windows/C# validation for the pushed draft branch\n\n## Remaining Goal Work\n- install a CI-built patched binary on a crabbox and rerun tray restart, Windows reboot, and Linux gateway restart identity checks\n- run the real interactive exec approval path: deny, allow once, allow always, and stale/drift protection",
